  <text>
    <body>
      <pb n="1"/>
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <date when="1873-07-16">July 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 3</date>
          </dateline>
          <salute>Dear <persName ref="#stillja">James</persName>:</salute>
        </opener>
        <p>
          As I have concluded to give<lb/> Mr. <persName>Somers</persName> an agency and want him to have<lb/> fair sailing suppose I send to you 4 dozen<lb/> books, and let him get them from you just<lb/> as he may want them. For instance, he<lb/> might want a few today to deliver<lb/> and you could let him have them on<lb/> paying the price cash down. Will this<lb/> be asking too much of you? If the trouble<lb/> will not be too great I think the plan<lb/> will work well. If you will allow<lb/> me I will send you one box for a trial.
        </p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours truly &amp; affectionately</salute>
          <signed><persName ref="#stillwi"><choice><abbr>W</abbr><expan>William </expan></choice> Still</persName></signed>
        </closer>
    </body>
  </text>
